# Agent routing

Before non-trivial work: read the matching skill (`SKILL.md`), then act. Delegate to a
subagent via `Task` when the task is multi-file, review-gated, or domain-heavy.

Full routing tables: `AGENTS.md` § Skills & subagents routing.

## Mandatory triggers

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Raw request / vague feature | Read `intake-to-spec` or run `speckit-specify` |
| New feature / component | Read `brainstorming` first |
| Before writing code | Read `test-driven-development`; read domain skill |
| Before custom utility | Read `search-first` |
| After code changes | Launch `code-reviewer` subagent |
| Auth / user input / secrets / API | Read `security-review`; launch `security-reviewer` |
| Asterisk / WebRTC / SIP / voice-bot | Read `voice-bot-stack` |
| Webshop / product page / checkout | Read `frontend-ui-ux` |
| UI polish / "feels off" | Read `make-interfaces-feel-better` |
| Before deploy | Read `pre-deploy-checklist` |
| Before accepting work | Read `review-and-verify` or launch `verifier` |

## Subagent quick pick

- `explore` — codebase search, unknown location
- `planner` — implementation plan, large refactor
- `architect` — system design, trade-offs
- `code-reviewer` — post-change review (required)
- `security-reviewer` — OWASP, secrets, auth
- `e2e-runner` — Playwright / critical flows
- `ui-ux-reviewer` — UI acceptance after implementation
- `verifier` — skeptical second pass before accept
- `shell` — git, docker, long command sequences
- `ci-investigator` — failed PR check diagnosis

## UI workflow

`brainstorming` → `frontend-ui-ux` → `make-interfaces-feel-better` → `ui-ux-reviewer`

## Do not skip

- Domain skills for voice-bot, FastAPI, React, Docker
- Review gate after implementation
- Security review on sensitive surfaces
